channel.title: Compile error
channel.description:
I was trying to add loyalty titles add I got this error:
[code]Loyalty.java:10: error: cannot find symbol public static final String TITLE_PATH = Config.CACHE_DIR + "titles.dat";
^ symbol: variable config location: class Loyalty Note: client.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Finished! Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Then I changed it and got this error:
[code]Loyalty.java:10: error: cannot find symbol public static final String TITLE_PATH = signlink.findcachedir() + "title s.dat"; ^ symbol: variable signlink location: class Loyalty Note: client.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
PLEASE HELP!!
